/*

modulo: x%y : it gives the remainder after dividing x/y

divisibility: if x%y==0 it means x is completely divisible by y

range: if we do x%y it means answer will be in the range [x....(y-1)]

remember:
if x<y then x%y=x
infinity: x%y == [0...(y-1)] => %y = [0...(y-1)] => %y =[0...(y-1)]

formulas: (a+b)%k = (a%k + b%k) %k

          (a*b)%k = (a%k * b%k) %k

          (a-b)%k = (a%k - b%k +k) %k



 (x%k)%k == (x% 2k)%k == (x% 3k)%k ==....







*/

